jdavidb.  20090507.  How do you stash an untracked file?  Stack overflow.
web http://stackoverflow.com/questions/835501/how-do-you-stash-an-untracked-file

Add (git add) the file and start tracking it.  Then stash.  Since the
entire contents of the file are new, they will be stashed, and you can
manipulate it as necessary.

As of version 1.7.7 you can use git stash -u to stash untracked files
without staging them.
